format

public static java.lang.String format(long value)
Format a relative millisecond time value as "hh:mm:ss.ms [+n days]". For example, a value of 2500 is returned as "00:00:02.0500", and a value of 172799999 is returned as "23:59:59.0999 +1 days"

Parameters:
value - Number of millseconds
Returns:
A relative time in the form "hh:mm:ss.ms [+n days]
